&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is a fast-growing comfort and lifestyle brand on a mission to make the world a cozier place. We are seeking a driven and relationship-oriented Bulk/Corporate Sales Account Executive to build and scale our corporate and bulk gifting channel—one of our fastest-growing revenue opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will own the full sales cycle for bulk and corporate accounts, from prospecting and outreach to close and account management. The ideal candidate brings a hunter mentality, strong relationship-building skills, and experience selling premium or lifestyle products to corporate buyers. This role reports directly to the Head of Commercial and is a key contributor to Lola&#39;s commercial growth strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales &amp;amp; Business Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect, qualify, and close new bulk and corporate accounts across gifting, employee appreciation, hospitality, and brand partnership use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the full sales cycle from initial outreach through contract and fulfillment handoff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a healthy pipeline; consistently meet or exceed monthly and quarterly revenue targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and nurture long-term relationships with key accounts to drive repeat purchasing and account expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for corporate clients, ensuring a seamless and premium experience from inquiry to delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track account performance and identify opportunities to upsell, cross-sell, or grow order volume over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Cross-Functional Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate CRM records; provide regular pipeline updates and revenue forecasts to the Head of Commercial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Product and Operations teams to ensure custom orders, timelines, and packaging requirements are executed to Lola&#39;s standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share market and customer insights to help inform product, pricing, and go-to-market strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in B2B sales, account management, or corporate gifting—ideally within a premium consumer goods or lifestyle brand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales targets in a quota-carrying role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and relationship-building skills; comfortable engaging with senior buyers and procurement leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter with excellent organizational skills and the ability to manage a high volume of accounts and outreach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial mindset; comfortable operating with ambiguity in a fast-growth environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with CRM tools (HubSpot, Salesforce, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive base salary and commission structure based on individual performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;21 days paid vacation + all federal holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full health benefits (health, dental, vision, mental)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;16 weeks paid birth parent leave; 8 weeks non-birth parent leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;55% off Lola Blankets for friends and family&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for career growth within Lola Blankets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Lola Blankets&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is a fast-growing, design-driven brand creating the world’s most loved faux-fur blankets. With a devoted community, strong influencer presence, and rapid scale, we are redefining what comfort and style mean for the home.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Role Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly creative and detail-oriented Color &amp;amp; Print Designer to drive seasonal color direction and print development across multiple categories, including blankets, sleepwear, and accessories. This role is critical in shaping the visual identity of the brand through distinctive color palettes, original prints, and commercially compelling seasonal concepts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate thrives in a fast-growing DTC environment and understands how to translate trend, consumer insight, and brand DNA into scalable, production-ready artwork and color stories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in New York City, with minimal travel required for product reviews and approvals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seasonal Concept Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the execution of seasonal color palettes and print direction aligned with brand strategy and assortment plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the the creation of digital mood boards, inspiration decks, and trend research presentations to support seasonal concept reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the full Product team to establish cohesive, brand-right color stories across categories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Print &amp;amp; Pattern Design&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design original prints and patterns across all categories for mainline and collaborations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop multiple colorway and scale options to support merchandising needs and margin targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare production-ready artwork files for vendor handoff, ensuring technical accuracy and repeat precision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Color Development &amp;amp; Production Execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the lab dip and print strike-off process, reviewing submissions for accuracy in tone, saturation, scale, and hand feel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, actionable feedback to vendors to ensure color consistency and print quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain color standards and oversee approvals through color trial and pre-production stages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Design, Merchandising, and Product Development to ensure alignment between creative direction and commercial objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product storytelling and visual assets for internal reviews and launch planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3+ years of experience at a fast-growing DTC apparel or home brand, at the Associate Designer or Designer level.Strong portfolio demonstrating print development, color storytelling, and multi-category execution.Deep understanding of textile printing techniques and production processes, including lab dips and print strike-offs from concept thru production phases.Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, Photoshop) and experience leveraging AI-based design platforms to accelerate ideation and iteration.Strong knowledge of repeat layouts, scale development, and color separation for production.Highly organized with strong project management skills and ability to manage multiple seasonal calendars simultaneously.Bachelor’s degree in Textile Design, Fashion Design, Graphic Design, or related field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive benefits package (health, dental, vision, PTO)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K with company match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is a fast-growing comfort and lifestyle brand on a mission to make the world a cozier place. Our service-oriented CX Representatives are the voice and face of Lola to our customers, helping them resolve any issues that arise quickly and effectively with a surprise-and-delight attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a Customer Experience Representative, you will be the frontline voice of our brand, providing exceptional support to our customers primarily via phone, as well as through email channels when available. You will handle inquiries with empathy, maturity, and efficiency, ensuring every customer feels heard and valued. This role requires the ability to troubleshoot issues, process order changes, and navigate our internal systems to deliver timely resolutions. Ideal candidates are strong communicators, quick learners, and customer-focused problem solvers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;changed&quot;&gt;This is a full-time role running August through January - our most important time of year. We hire seasonally because we want every person on the team to be the right fit before we commit long-term. Strong performers who align with our culture and deliver results don&#39;t just finish the contract. They become part of the team. Conversion to a permanent role is based on performance and business needs, and it&#39;s something we actively pursue with the right people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide friendly, professional, and efficient customer support primarily via phone, as well as through email and text when available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Listen actively to customer concerns, demonstrate empathy, and work toward effective solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process order changes, refunds, replacements, and other account adjustments using internal systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve customer issues related to orders, shipping, billing, product inquiries, and more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately document customer interactions and escalate complex issues when necessary, following all published SOPs from CX Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay responsive, attentive, and up to date on company updates, policies, products, and processes to provide informed support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a positive team environment by sharing insights and feedback to improve customer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weekend Availability: &lt;/strong&gt;This role requires weekend availability on a rotational basis. Agents are scheduled for approximately one month of weekend shifts every 3-4 months. During an active rotation, agents work a Friday–Tuesday shift schedule for the duration of that rotation (approximately 4-5 weeks). Weekend rotations are planned in advance so agents have ample time to prepare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In regard to location, candidates in LA, NYC, or Salt Lake City are preferred. Additionally, we’re open to remote in AL, TN, CA, ID, NY, PA, TX, UT, IL, FL. If this sounds like you, we&#39;d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding verbal and written communication skills with a customer-first mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly learn and reliably use standard customer service technology platforms (Gorgias, Shopify, Slack, Email, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous phone support experience is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High empathy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and detail-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eagerness to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to take constructive feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Lola Blankets&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is a fast-growing, design-driven brand creating the world’s most loved faux-fur blankets. With a devoted community, strong influencer presence, and rapid scale, we are redefining what comfort and style mean for the home.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is looking for a Customer Lifecycle Director who will redefine what retention means for a premium, emotionally resonant brand. This is not a conventional “email and SMS” retention role. We’re looking for a leader who understands how to build brand love, loyalty, community, and advocacy — not just automate flows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will architect Lola’s full post-purchase journey, combining data, brand storytelling, community-building, and experiential touchpoints. They will partner deeply with the Brand team to create high-value, memorable experiences that turn customers into lifelong advocates and active participants in the Lola universe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll build what loyalty means for our brand — including the strategy, structure, and launch of a new loyalty program. This role is perfect for someone who has built retention engines at high-growth consumer brands, luxury brands, or top agencies — and who believes loyalty is earned through connection, creativity, and consistency, not just discounts and email triggers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end lifecycle strategy, ensuring every stage of the customer journey deepens connection and drives repeat behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and launch Lola’s loyalty program, including structure, tiers, benefits, and ongoing engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the retention and loyalty strategy component of our digital products: the website and mobile app.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Brand and Creative to design storytelling moments, VIP touchpoints, and experiential retention initiatives (events, access, exclusive drops).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop segmentation, personalization, and analytics frameworks that inform lifecycle strategy and measure LTV, repeat rate, and cohort performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead lifecycle channels (email, SMS, direct mail) and manage CRM/loyalty tech stack while innovating beyond traditional tactics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Sr. Retention Marketing Manager and future retention associates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive cross-functional alignment with Brand, Product, Ecomm, CX, and Paid Media to ensure a unified customer ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years in lifecycle, retention, or loyalty marketing at a high-growth DTC brand, luxury brand, or top-tier agency including 3+ years of management experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience building or operating successful loyalty programs or community-driven customer ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to create experiential, brand-led retention moments (events, VIP access, exclusive offerings).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills with Brand/Creative teams and an ability to blend storytelling with performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills — expertise in segmentation, cohort analysis, and LTV-based strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of owning the lifecycle roadmap and delivering measurable improvements in repeat purchase and retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;21 days paid vacation + most federal holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive health, dental, and vision coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;16 weeks paid birth parent leave; 8 weeks for non-birth parents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;55% off Lola Blankets for friends and family&lt;/

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is a fast-growing comfort and lifestyle brand on a mission to make the world a cozier place. We are seeking a Director of Inventory Planning &amp;amp; Allocation - Commercial to support our fast-growing, commercial business unit spanning wholesale, bulk, and retail sale channels. This role will be responsible for forecasting multi-channel inventory needs, managing on-order and on-hand inventory to optimize sales, margin, and service levels across wholesale, bulk orders, and owned retail channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is highly analytical and detail-oriented with extensive experience in fast-growing DTC brands, adept at multi-channel, multi-category ladder plans, and skilled in leveraging virtual warehouses to maximize efficiency and flexibility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory Planning &amp;amp; Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain demand forecasts in partnership with cross-functional teams, incorporating sales trends, product launches, product lifecycles, and promotional plans to inform purchasing and financial planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and optimize ladder plans across multiple channels and product categories, enabling daily thru annual sales and receipt unit needs at channel, category, style and SKU levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Place purchase orders and manage on-order pipelines to ensure balance inventory levels and timely demand fulfillment while minimizing excess inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory levels and recommend replenishment strategies to maximize availability and reduce stockouts or overstocking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify risks and opportunities in inventory and recommend actions to support business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage greige and liability fabric on-hand and consumption. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Allocation &amp;amp; Distribution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allocate inventory across wholesale, bulk, and retail channels based on demand forecasts and sales priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage virtual warehouse inventory strategies to support flexibility in fulfillment and optimize working capital.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with logistics and operations teams to ensure accurate distribution and inventory visibility across the network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Commercial, Merchandising, Operations, Marketing and Finance teams to align inventory strategies with assortment plans, sales goals, and margin objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide weekly and monthly reporting on inventory health, channel performance, and forecast accuracy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of inventory planning, allocation, or related roles at fast-growing DTC brands, with proven success at the Senior Manager or Director level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong track record managing multi-channel, multi-category ladder plans and working with virtual warehouses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to deliver accurate daily, monthly, quarterly, and annual sales and receipt projections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in forecasting, financial modeling, and inventory optimization; advanced Excel skills required, ERP experience a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of DTC and omnichannel distribution dynamics, including ecommerce, wholesale, and international markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent cross-functional communication and problem-solving skills; ability to balance data-driven decisions with brand priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;W

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly strategic and collaborative Director of Merchandising to lead category strategy from concept through go-to-market execution. This role will play a critical role in shaping the product assortment, identifying whitespace opportunities, and building commercially successful product strategies across a growing multi-category business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has deep expertise in assortment strategy within a fast-growing, multi-channel DTC brand and possesses a strong balance of analytical rigor, consumer intuition, and cross-functional leadership. This role requires a highly proactive and entrepreneurial mindset, with the ability to influence senior leadership, build alignment across teams, and operate effectively in a dynamic growth environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Category Strategy &amp;amp; Assortment Planning&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Head of Product &amp;amp; Merchandising to define the assortment strategy across multiple product categories, identifying opportunities for growth, innovation, and building customer LTV.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain line plans that support balanced assortments across key classifications, price points, and customer segments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Creation &amp;amp; Commercialization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Design and Product Development to ideate and develop new product opportunities, tied directly to assortment strategy and strategic growth plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sourcing / Product Development to align product strategies with production capabilities and timeline requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish retail pricing strategies and margin architecture across new product initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all product specifications, merchandising details, and assortment data are accurately created and maintained within systems and development tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep a finger on the cultural pulse and competitive landscape. Translate trends and white space opportunities with a Lola lens rather than chasing or copying them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Planning &amp;amp; Opportunity Sizing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance and Planning to evaluate and size new product opportunities and growth initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize sales data, customer insights, and market trends to inform assortment decisions and investment priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop category hindsight and forward-looking recommendations to optimize productivity and inventory efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Go-to-Market Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Brand Marketing, Performance Marketing, and Operations to develop comprehensive go-to-market strategies for product launches and seasonal drops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment between product storytelling, launch timing, inventory readiness, and marketing objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support campaign planning with compelling product narratives and assortment positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Analysis &amp;amp; Lifecycle Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze product performance post-launch, evaluating success against financial and customer metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to accelerate performance through pricing actions, marketing support, product refinements, or lifecycle management strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present category insights and recommendations to senior leadership on a regular basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lola Blankets is a fast-growing comfort and lifestyle brand on a mission to make the world a cozier place. We are seeking an Influencer Marketing Manager to lead and optimize the brand’s reach. This role involves strategic management of influencer identification, recruitment, contracting, onboarding, and compensation–in addition to being a thought leader for Lola’s digital marketing efforts broadly. You will work closely with the creative and marketing teams to elevate the brand’s influencer marketing strategy. Lola Blankets is a small but growing team – giving lots of opportunity to plug in across functions and grow with the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Lola’s paid influencer partnerships, leading in sales calendar, identification, outreach/recruitment, contracting, onboarding, and compensation using the influencer CRM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage affiliate platforms, and work alongside our Performance Marketing Team and Community Manager (for e.g.: ShopMy &amp;amp; LTK campaigns)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own influencer contracts &amp;amp; negotiations, partnering with legal to make sure creators are FTC compliant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Performance Marketing to find &amp;amp; source influencers who can create dedicated whitelist content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and track social media key performance indicators (KPIs) for influencer marketing - emphasis on dividing campaigns by brand awareness &amp;amp; sales driving campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with Influencer &amp;amp; Social Director on influencer collaboration product strategy and PR&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the main point of contact for all influencers and focus on building relationships with creators (communicate via DMs, email, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Senior Community &amp;amp; Ambassador Manager on gifting creators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize influencer PR events (3-5 per year)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with external vendors to create high caliber influencer &amp;amp; PR package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a thought leader for paid digital marketing broadly, including platforms such as Facebook, Instagram, Pinterest, and TikTok&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role will report to the Director of Influencer &amp;amp; Social. It will be hybrid with 3 days per week in either our NYC or Utah office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Marketing, Communications, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in influencer marketing, with a focus on campaign management and strategy development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong creative and critical thinking skills, and a proven track record of successful influencer campaigns that drive brand awareness, engagement, and sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with paid advertising teams and working with influencers across a variety media platforms: IG, FB, TikTok, Podcast marketing, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of social media platforms, influencer marketing trends, and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to build and maintain strong relationships with influencers and internal stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical mindset with the ability to define and track KPIs, providing data-driven insights and recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and detail-oriented, with the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
