&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong creative sensibilities with exceptional project management skills and deep experience managing packaging and trim development within a fast-growing DTC consumer brand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a highly detail-oriented individual who can successfully manage multiple initiatives simultaneously across New Product Introduction (NPI), seasonal launches, collaborations, and fast-track development calendars.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and development of all product-specific packaging and trims including but not limited to labels, trims, inserts, gifting components, belly bands, sleeves, hangtags, care labels, woven labels, embroidery applications, vessels, zipper pulls, polybags, gifting boxes and other branded elements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Design, Merchandising, and Brand Marketing teams to define project requirements and creative direction, and manage packaging and trim development from concept through production approval.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage packaging and trim development calendars across NPI, seasonal, replenishment, and fast-track development programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all packaging and trim elements align with brand standards, efficiency objectives, customer expectations, and business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
