&lt;li&gt;Lead sample reviews and approval processes to ensure all components meet design intent, quality standards, and production requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and approve color standards, material submissions, strike-offs, proofs, and production samples.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead packaging and trim review meetings as part of the overall product development process, communicating project status, risks, and recommendations to stakeholders and leadership teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new materials, finishes, structures, and packaging solutions, sourcing new vendors, materials, and capabilities to support product and brand growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for all packaging and trim suppliers, managing communications related to development, costing, timelines, quality expectations, and approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate costs and development timelines and ensure vendors meet key milestone dates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot supplier issues and proactively resolve development challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and support quality control processes for packaging and trims.&lt;/li&gt;
